The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Lake Almanor West had a population of 211. The population density was {{convert|92.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lake Almanor West was 191 (90.5%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (0.5%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.5%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 1 (0.5%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 17 (8.1%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 2 persons (0.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Lake Almanor West CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0639425 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 114 households, out of which 16 (14.0%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 73 (64.0%) were married-couple households, 9 (7.9%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 16 (14.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 16 (14.0%) had a male householder with no partner present. 26 households (22.8%) were one person, and 16 (14.0%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.85.<ref name=DP1/> There were 84 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (73.7% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Lake Almanor West CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0639425 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 15 people (7.1%) under the age of 18, 17 people (8.1%) aged 18 to 24, 25 people (11.8%) aged 25 to 44, 49 people (23.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 105 people (49.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 64.8{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 108.9 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 498 housing units at an average density of {{convert|217.8|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 114 (22.9%) were occupied. Of these, 91 (79.8%) were owner-occupied, and 23 (20.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0639425|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715030359/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0639425|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Lake Almanor West CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Lake Almanor West had a population of 270. The population density was {{convert|118.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lake Almanor West was 259 (95.9%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1 (0.4%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 1 (0.4%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 1 (0.4%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 1 (0.4%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 7 (2.6%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 11 persons (4.1%).

The Census reported that 270 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 134 households, out of which 8 (6.0%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 108 (80.6%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 3 (2.2%) had a female householder with no husband present, 2 (1.5%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 3 (2.2%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 20 households (14.9%) were made up of individuals, and 13 (9.7%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.01.  There were 113 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (84.3% of all households); the average family size was 2.17.

The population was spread out, with 12 people (4.4%) under the age of 18, 3 people (1.1%) aged 18 to 24, 16 people (5.9%) aged 25 to 44, 99 people (36.7%) aged 45 to 64, and 140 people (51.9%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 65.4 years. For every 100 females, there were 107.7 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 106.4 males.

There were 475 housing units at an average density of {{convert|207.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 129 (96.3%) were owner-occupied, and 5 (3.7%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 7.2%; the rental vacancy rate was 40.0%.  261 people (96.7% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 9 people (3.3%) lived in rental housing units.

